5.2 Steps in Chemical Evolution (Abiogenesis)
Step What Happened
Step 1 Formation of simple inorganic molecules (H2O, CO2, NH3, CH4) in early atmosphere
Step 2 Energy sources (UV rays, lightning, volcanic heat) trigger reactions
Step 3 Formation of simple organic molecules (amino acids, sugars, nucleotides)
Step 4 Formation of complex organic molecules (proteins, nucleic acids) — polymerisation
Step 5 Self-replication of RNA (RNA World hypothesis — RNA came before DNA)
Step 6 Formation of proto-cells / coacervates (lipid membranes enclosing organic molecules)
Step 7 Evolution of metabolism — first true prokaryotic cells (~3.5 BYA)
